NFS Underground 2 Online - stock client error dialogs
=====================================================

This file documents the stock dialogs seen when the server sends forced
20922 auth/persona reject frames. Use the code in the left column with the
admin commands documented in docs/CONFIG.md:

  authcode <code> <account|*>
  personacode <code> <persona|*> [uses]


AUTH / LOGIN
------------

The server sends these as auth<code> frames.

1. imst - invalid/missing account
   Dialog: "Invalid name/account."
   Server reasons: unknown_account, missing_identifier, invalid_auth.

2. logn - account already logged in
   Dialog: "Already logged on server."
   Server reasons: account_in_use, already_logged_in, already_online.

3. lock - locked/disabled account
   Dialog: "The EA account is locked and cannot be used. Please contact EA
   Customer Support."
   Server reasons: account_locked, account_disabled, rate_limited.

4. pass - invalid password
   Dialog: "The specified password is invalid."
   Server reasons: bad_password, missing_password, password_error.

5. ikey - CD key/account key problem
   Dialog: "The EA account has not been authenticated with a CD key. You must
   lock your CD key to an EA account before you can play online. A CD key can
   only be locked to one EA account, and the process cannot be undone. Do you
   want to lock your CD key to this EA account?"
   Notes: this is a yes/no prompt in the client, not a hard disconnect dialog
   by itself.
   Server reasons: invalid_key, bad_key, invalid_cdkey, invalid_cd_key.

6. tosa - Terms of Service required
   Dialog: forces the Terms of Service flow even if account creation is not
   being used.
   Server reasons: tos_not_accepted, terms_not_accepted.

7. dber - backend/database/server-side auth failure
   Dialog: "The EA server is currently experiencing technical difficulties.
   Please try again later. If the problem persists, please contact EA Customer
   Support."
   Server reasons: database_error, backend_error, save_failed, no_accounts,
   server_full.

8. blak - banned/blocked account
   Dialog: "This account has been banned."
   Server reasons: admin_ban, banned, blacklisted, blacklist, blocked.

9. shar - share/privacy agreement required
   Observed dialog: same generic lobby-server login failure as below on this
   client build.
   Server reasons: share_not_accepted, share_required.

10. miss - missing required login fields
    Observed dialog: same generic lobby-server login failure as below.
    Server reasons: missing_fields, missing_required_fields.

11. filt - account/name text filter failure
    Observed dialog: same generic lobby-server login failure as below.
    Server reasons: filtered, filter_failed, profane.

12. time - auth backend timeout
    Observed dialog: same generic lobby-server login failure as below.
    Server reasons: auth_timeout, timeout, backend_timeout.

13. over - invalid auth backend state
    Observed dialog: same generic lobby-server login failure as below.
    Server reasons: invalid_state, backend_over.

Generic login failure text for codes 9-13:
"The lobby server login failed. The server may be down or there may be network
problems preventing a connection this time. Check your network settings and try
again later."


PERSONA SELECT
--------------

The server sends these as pers<code> frames. Normal login usually uses the
select-persona path, so use these codes when testing an existing persona.

1. persinvp - invalid persona / persona not allowed for account
   Dialog: "There was a problem selecting this persona. You will be returned
   to the EA login screen."
   Server reasons: invp, invalid persona, account/persona mismatch.

2. persmaut - persona selected before auth is complete
   Observed dialog: same as persinvp.
   Server reasons: maut, missing auth.

3. perspset - persona policy/blacklist rejection
   Observed dialog: same as persinvp.
   Server reasons: pset, policy set/blacklist hit.


CREATE PERSONA
--------------

The server sends these as cper<code> frames. These only apply when the client is
creating a new persona and sends cper.

1. cperdupl - duplicate persona
   Dialog: "This persona is already taken. Please try a different name."
   Server reasons: dupl, active duplicate persona.

2. cperinvp - invalid persona
   Dialog: "There was an error creating this persona."
   Server reasons: invp, invalid characters, empty name, too long, blacklist
   when configured to use invp.

3. cpernspc - no persona slot available
   Observed dialog: same as cperinvp.
   Server reasons: nspc, persona slot limit reached.
